  "text": "More generally, suppose we label the bosons φ 1 , . . . , φ m and the fermions ψ 1 , . . . , ψ m . Choose an integer I with 1 ≤ I ≤ N , and an integer A with 1 ≤ A ≤ m. For each such pair of integers, we consider the transformation rules for Q I on the boson φ A , and we might expect that these will be of the form [CITATION_1] where c = ±1, λ = 0 or 1, and B is an integer with 1 ≤ B ≤ m, so that ψ B is some fermion; each of c, λ, B will, in general, depend on I and A. Note that",
